race.comment: BROADWAY LANE (7) looks to have found a nice race to win another. He is a winner at this track and has placed in three of his four runs at this track and distance. He will roll forward for Milnes and make his own luck. In an even race, he's a winning chance. SETTEVELI (1) is down in grade and has more upside than most of these. Stable is really picking up momentum and expect him to be in the finish. SWISSTA (8) mixes his form but is a place chance, while PEPERONCINO (5) is another worth some thought for quaddies and wider plays. UTAH JOE (6) is fitter after an average run first-up and gets a 2kg claim here. In the mix also.
